  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0db6\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dad\u0dc4\u0db1\u0db8 \u0dad\u0dc0\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd3\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9d \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cabral's foreign ban is extended",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo Additional Magistrate Harshana Kekunawela today (25) ordered to extend the ban of former Central Bank Governor Mr. Ajith Nivard Cabral, who is banned from traveling abroad in connection with the alleged bond fraud incident, until the 26th of October.",
        "These facts were presented when the Magistrate's inquiry related to this incident was called before the court again.",
        "President's lawyer Shavendra Fernando appeared before the court on behalf of the former central bank governor.",
        "A personal complaint related to this incident was presented before the court by Mr. Rajith Keerthi Tennakoon, a resident of Rajagiriya, who served as the Governor of the Southern and Central Provinces.",
        "The plaintiff informed the court through an affidavit that former Central Bank Governor Ajit Nivard Cabral was charged with criminal breach of trust, criminal breach of trust by a banker, dishonest and misappropriation of money, bearing No. 07 of 1937. (Amended) Ordinance No. 56 (a) (1) (a) that an offense has been committed."
      ],
